CIVIC INNOVATION LICENSE

Version 1.0

PREAMBLE

The Civic Innovation License (CIL) is a free, copyleft license designed specifically for software created by open source communities operating within or in support of government, public sector institutions, non profit 501(c)(3) organizations, public benefit corporations and individuals, for the direct benefit of all citizens. It is rooted in the principles of the GNU General Public License version 2.0 (GPL-2.0), extended with provisions that reflect the public nature and civic mission of this class of software.

The fundamental principle of this license is that civic software — software developed for the public good using public or community resources — must remain a public asset. It must remain open, accessible, and freely available to be studied, modified, and redistributed. However, it must never become a vehicle for private commercial gain. Civic software belongs to the people.

When we speak of "free software," we refer to freedom, not price. This license is designed to guarantee your freedom to share and change civic software — and to ensure that any software derived from civic work remains equally free and equally civic in purpose.

To protect these rights, this license makes clear that no one may take civic software and use it for private commercial advantage. Private for-profit enterprises may not use, redistribute, or build upon software covered by this license for commercial purposes. Permitted entities are restricted to government bodies, public agencies, registered non-profit organizations, public benefit corporations, individuals, and publicly owned enterprises operating in the interest of citizens.

The precise terms and conditions for copying, distribution, modification, and use follow below.

SECTION 1 — DEFINITIONS

For the purposes of this License, the following definitions apply:

"This License" refers to Version 1.0 of the Civic Innovation License (CIL-1.0).

"The Program" refers to any copyrightable work licensed under this License.

"You" (or "Your") refers to any individual or legal entity exercising rights granted by this License.

"Civic Software" means software developed by or on behalf of open source communities operating in connection with government, public institutions or individuals, intended to serve the public interest.

"Permitted Entity" means any of the following:
(a) A government body or public agency at any level (local, regional, national, or supra-national);
(b) A registered non-profit organization recognized under applicable law (including 501(c)(3) organizations in the United States and their equivalents in other jurisdictions);
(c) A public benefit corporation or community interest company, incorporated with a legal mandate to operate for the public good and not primarily for the financial benefit of shareholders or members;
(d) A publicly owned enterprise in which the majority ownership interest is held by one or more government bodies;
(e) An individual or volunteer contributor acting in a non-commercial civic or educational capacity.

"Commercial Use" means use of the Program primarily intended for or directed toward commercial advantage or monetary compensation, including but not limited to: use by for-profit corporations, integration into commercial products or services, or deployment in environments operated for profit, except where such use falls within the definition of Permitted Entity above.

"Source Code" means the preferred form of the Program for making modifications, including all associated interface definition files, scripts used to control compilation, and installation.

"Derivative Work" means any work that is based on or derived from the Program, including translations, modifications, adaptations, or any work that incorporates all or a portion of the Program.

