SECTION 12 — CIVIC EQUITY AND ACCESSIBILITY

In the spirit of the civic mission of this License, contributors and distributors are strongly encouraged — and where required by applicable law are obligated — to ensure that Civic Software is:

	•	Accessible to people with disabilities, in conformance with applicable accessibility standards (such as WCAG 2.1 AA or national equivalents);
	•	Available in all official languages of the jurisdiction in which it is deployed, where practicable;
	•	Designed with the privacy and security of citizen data as a primary concern;
	•	Non-discriminatory in its design and operation, serving all segments of the public equitably;
	•	Transparent in its operation and decision-making logic, especially when used in government decisions affecting citizens.

These are aspirational standards rooted in the civic purpose of this License. Failure to meet these standards does not, by itself, constitute a violation of the License, but developers and deployers of Civic Software are expected to strive toward them as a matter of civic ethics and responsibility.

