You may not copy, modify, sublicense, or distribute the Program except as expressly provided under this License. Any attempt otherwise to copy, modify, sublicense, or distribute the Program is void, and will automatically terminate your rights under this License.

However, parties who have received copies, or rights, from you under this License will not have their licenses terminated so long as such parties remain in full compliance.

If a non-Permitted Entity uses the Program in violation of this License, the copyright holders may pursue all available legal remedies, including injunctive relief and damages. Additionally, the violating entity shall be required to immediately cease all use of the Program and destroy all copies in their possession.

The stewardship body of this License may issue written exceptions to the civic use restriction upon application, subject to conditions it deems appropriate to preserve the civic character of the software.

SECTION 14 — FUTURE VERSIONS OF THIS LICENSE

Midnite Limited Liability Company or the successor entity may publish revised and/or new versions of the Civic Innovation License from time to time. Such new versions will be similar in spirit to the present version but may address new legal, technical, or civic concerns.

Each version is given a distinguishing version number. If the Program specifies that it is governed by a specific version of the Civic Innovation License, you may use the Program only under the terms of that version. If the Program specifies "any later version," you may choose to follow the terms of any later version published by the Open Civic Commons.

If the Program does not specify a version number of the Civic Innovation License, then the latest version of the license applies.

SECTION 15 — HOW TO APPLY THIS LICENSE TO YOUR WORK

To apply the Civic Innovation License to your work, attach the following notices to the program. It is safest to attach them to the start of each source file to most effectively state the exclusion of warranty; each file should have at least the "copyright" line and a pointer to where the full notice is found.

<One line to give the program's name and a brief idea of what it does.>
Copyright (C) <year> <name of author>

This program is Civic Software licensed under the Civic Innovation License v1.0.
It may only be used by Permitted Entities (governments, non-profits,
public benefit corporations, and publicly owned enterprises).
Commercial use by for-profit entities is strictly prohibited.

You should have received a copy of the Civic Innovation License
along with this program. If not, see <https://civiccommons.org/licenses/cil-1.0>.

Also add information on how to contact you by electronic and paper mail. If your civic project has a project management committee or governance board, provide contact information for that body as well.
